{{orphan|date=November 2007}} {{nihongo|'''Taga Taisha'''|多賀大社}}, also {{nihongo|'''Taga Jinja'''|多賀神社}} is a [[Shinto]] [[Jinja (Shinto)|shrine]] located in [[Taga, Shiga|Taga]], [[Shiga Prefecture|Shiga]] in [[Japan]] and sacred to [[Izanagi]] and [[Izanami]]. It is popular with the graces of long life, good marriage and fortune. The locals nickname the shrine "''[[Honorific speech in Japanese#Honorific prefixes|O]]-taga [[Japanese titles#San|san]]''" with honor and intimacy. [[File:Taga taisha1.JPG|thumb|250px|Main Shrine of Taga Taisha]] {{Shinto}}
==History== This ancient shrine is old enough that it was mentioned in the ''[[Kojiki]]''. According to that text it dates from AD620, having been built during a time when [[Buddhism]] and Shinto were both doing very well. It contains both a Buddhist temple and Shinto shrine. The shrine has beautiful garden and a stone bridge, which were constructed by [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] as an offering for his mother's long life. It is next to the study attached to the Shrine offices.
==Festival== *{{nihongo|'''Korei Taisai'''|古例大祭}} - Most important festival feld on April 23. Also name {{nihongo|'''Taga Matsuri'''|多賀まつり}}. *{{nihongo|'''Otaue-sai'''|御田植祭}} - A festival of planting rice with traditional rites feld on June 7. *{{nihongo|'''Mantō-sai'''|万灯祭}} - A lantern festival feld on the night of August 3-5.
==Specialty== *{{nihongo|'''Otaga shakushi'''|お多賀杓子}} - A talisman shakushi (Japanese [[Ladle (spoon)|ladle]]) from [[Empress Genshō]] age. It is said the the origin of a Japanese word ''Otamajakushi''. *{{nihongo|'''Itokiri-mochi'''|糸切餅}} - A [[mochi]] [[wagashi]] sold at souvenir shops around the shrine. It is said that Itokiri-mochi came from a celebration food of [[Mongol invasions of Japan|Japanese victory to Mongol]]
==Gallery== <gallery> Image:Tagataishasmallshrine1.JPG|Small Shrine with ancient artifact horse statue Image:Kaguraden-taga-taisha.JPG|Kagura-den (noh stage) for small blessing ceremonies and social activities Image:Tagataisha-rockgarden.JPG|Rock Garden Image:Tagataisharockbridge.JPG|Stone Bridge </gallery>
==Data== *English Name: Taga Shrine *Address: Taga, [[Taga, Shiga|Taga-cho]], [[Inukami District, Shiga|Inukami-gun]], [[Shiga Prefecture|Shiga-ken]] *Postal Code: 522-03 *Telephone Number: 0749-48-1101 *Latitude/Longitude: lat=35.2; long=136.333 (35.2 12' 00" N 136.333 20' 00) *Construction Date: Around AD620 (According to the Kojiki) *Access: About 20 minutes walk from [[Ohmi Railway]] [[Ohmi Railway Taga Line|Taga Line]] [[Taga Taisha-mae Station]], or about 10 minutes bus from [[West Japan Railway|JR West]] [[Biwako Line]][[Minami-Hikone Station]]. {{coord|35|22|54|N|136|29|10|E|region:JP_scale:30000_source:jawiki|display=title}}
